KOCH lowers U . S . posted crude prices 50 cts / bbl . Koch Oil said it cut the price it will pay for U . S . crude oil by 50 cents a barrel , effective Oct 29 . The decrease brings the new price for U . S . benchmark grade West Texas Intermediate to $ 22 . 75 a barrel , and West Texas Sour to $ 20 . 75 a barrel . Light Louisiana sweet crude is now $ 22 . 75 a barrel , and Oklahoma sweet is $ 22 . 75 . - - New York Energy Desk , + 1 212 859 - 1620 
